# missiontools Changelog


## 0.2.0

### New Features

- InterferenceAnalysis class for space network interference risk assessment,
  supporting victim/interfering constellation analysis with SC<->SC, SC<->GS,
  and GS<->GS link types. Includes result caching and interference_percentage()
  method for cumulative interference plots.

- Condition system: new missiontools.condition subpackage with AbstractCondition
  ABC (boolean time-domain predicates with LRU caching) and seven concrete
  condition classes: SunlightCondition, SubSatelliteRegionCondition,
  VisibilityCondition, AndCondition, OrCondition, NotCondition, XorCondition.
  Boolean operators (&, |, ^, ~) enable ergonomic composition.

- ConditionAttitudeLaw: routes between child attitude laws based on a
  priority-ordered list of (condition, law) pairs, falling through to a
  default when no condition holds.

- RectangularSensor: pyramidal field-of-view defined by two orthogonal
  half-angles, extending the sensor hierarchy alongside ConicSensor.

- Sensor condition support: optional condition attribute on sensors that gates
  when a sensor contributes to coverage, with edge-refined bisection for
  detecting active intervals over a time window.

- SymmetricAntenna.from_s465: ITU-R S.465 reference Earth station antenna
  pattern factory method, supporting canonical sidelobe envelope and smooth
  parabolic main-lobe variants. Includes gmax_dbi override parameter.

- AttitudeLaw limb mode: grazing-tangent pointing at a configurable altitude
  offset above the central body, with analytical tangent solve in ECEF
  accounting for WGS84 oblateness.

- AttitudeLaw custom mode: user-supplied callback with signature
  (t, r_eci, v_eci) -> (N,4) quaternions for full 3-DOF attitude control.

- GroundStation tracking in TrackAttitudeLaw: targets can now be either
  Spacecraft or GroundStation (geodetic position converted to ECI at each
  timestep).

- ecef_to_geodetic: WGS84 inverse geodetic transform via Bowring's method.

- New example notebooks: interference_analysis.ipynb, conditional_coverage.ipynb,
  and updated canada_coverage.ipynb.


### Refactoring

- AttitudeLaw refactored from a single mode-dispatching class into an
  AbstractAttitudeLaw ABC with concrete subclasses: FixedAttitudeLaw,
  TrackAttitudeLaw, CustomAttitudeLaw, LimbAttitudeLaw.

- Sensor refactored from a flat module into a sensor/ subpackage with
  AbstractSensor ABC and ConicSensor subclass (mirrors attitude pattern).

- coverage.py split into sampling.py, visibility.py, and coverage.py.

- propagate_analytical split into _propagate_twobody and _propagate_j2.

- CoverageConstraints dataclass introduced to reduce parameter passing in
  coverage API.

- Extracted shared host_eci_state() and geodetic_up() utility functions.

- Moved _J2000_US to constants.py.

- Standardized _deg suffix for degree-valued parameters in public API.

- Standardized point_density to km² everywhere.

- Attachment guards added to add_sensor, add_solar_config, add_thermal_config.


### Bug Fixes

- Fixed _limb_direction GMST recomputation (5x redundant -> 1x via
  eci_ecef_rotation).
- Fixed central_body_radius default to EARTH_SEMI_MAJOR_AXIS.
- Fixed J2 branch raan/arg_p scalar overwrite.
- Fixed IsotropicAntenna missing super().__init__() call.
- Fixed NormalVectorSolarConfig.oap() datetime64/datetime conversion breaking
  timedelta64 arithmetic.
- Fixed np.trapezoid -> np.trapz for numpy compatibility.
- Added validation for seconds in _parse_hms.
- Improved error messages for eccentricity bounds.


## 0.1.0 - Initial release
